CNCP v1 23929
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#4245: $emit loses `this` context on external methods",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:25.502030+00:00",
  "text": "$emit loses `this` context on external methods\n\n### Version\r\n3.1.5\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[https://sfc.vuejs.org/#eyJBcHAudn....](https://sfc.vuejs.org/#)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nOpen Developer Tools, click on each button and see what gets shown for `this`.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nExecution of an event handler should have a consistent context handling for `this`.\r\nAs seen with Vue 2.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nIf we execute a custom event by using `$emit`, the context behaves different than just using events like `@click`.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: compiler",
    "has workaround"
  ],
